fix(auth): :bug: handle null record in findById

Why:
UserService.findById() throws a null pointer exception when
querying for a user ID that does not exist in the database.
This causes silent request failures and poor user experience
when looking up missing user accounts.

What:
Add null check after database query and return a proper 404
response with descriptive error message to the caller instead
of allowing the exception to propagate up the stack.

Ticket: PROJ-247
Signed-off-by: Alice Developer <alice@example.com>
